### Promoting Awareness of Riaz Counseling and Other Support Services

A critical role for colleges is to actively promote awareness of all available mental health support options, both on and off campus. Students can't use resources they don't know exist. This means regularly communicating about the university's counseling center and other on-campus support services through email, social media, and orientations.

In addition to internal resources, it's beneficial for institutions to inform students about external options. Highlighting trusted local practices, such as Riaz Counseling, gives students more choices to find a mental health counselor who is the right fit for them. This is especially important when on-campus services have long waitlists or may not offer specialized care.

By actively promoting a wide range of services, colleges create a comprehensive safety net. This ensures that every student, no matter their specific need or situation, knows where they can turn for professional help. This proactive approach to awareness is a cornerstone of effective mental health support on campus.

