## Conclusion

If you are a college student in **Houston, Texas**, feeling the profound weight of burnout, know that change is possible. The solution is not to simply "try harder," but to stop, assess, and change your relationship with your work and your well-being.

Your potential is defined by your capacity for growth, not by your current level of exhaustion. By recognizing the signs of burnout and actively seeking the right support, you can turn a moment of crisis into a turning point for resilience.

